    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "12.\nPOS\nBUY U.S. SAVINGS\nSTATES\nBONDS POSTAGE\nASK YOU POSTE\nADDRESS\n11 CENT\n1417 Fouleran\nSax . На.",
      "Have You Ever Traveled Aboard a Flying Clipper Ship?\nBuilt for service over ocean routes these huge\nstream-lined flying boats, weighing 19 tons, are\naerial giants, their four engines more powerful than\nan average locomotive, their dimensions larger than\nships in which Columbus first crossed the Atlantic...\nEach carries a crew of six, Captain and three flying\nofficers, a purser and cabin steward. In their four\nspacious cabins, sound-proofed, ventilated, are\nroomy accommodations for thirty-two passengers.\nOver the romantic trails of Columbus, of Spanish\nConquistadores, of swashbuckling pirateers, of\n\"Clipper Ships\"\nof another age, you speed along\nradio-guarded routes to arrive at your destination,\nentranced at the ease of your passage, refreshed\nand enthusiastic for the holiday ahead-just as more\nthan five hundred thousand other Pan American\npassengers have flown two hundred million miles\nalong these airways that link the Americas.\nDRIES SISTENE"
    ],
